# ── Database ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Hosted Postgres (Neon/Supabase free tier for the pilot).
# - Migrations & seeds run as the OWNER role:      DATABASE_URL_OWNER (or DATABASE_URL while provisioning)
# - The app runs as the restricted `aps_runtime` role (created by `npm run db:harden`,
#   NO BYPASSRLS — row-level security applies). Always sslmode=verify-full
#   (require/prefer/verify-ca are normalized to verify-full in code — pg@9 pin).
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://aps_runtime:CHANGE_ME@host:5432/aps?sslmode=verify-full"

# ── Clerk (auth) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Absent keys in local development → guarded dev-auth mode (cookie user switcher).
# Absent keys in ANY deployed environment (Vercel/CI) → the app refuses to start.
# Never prefix secrets with NEXT_PUBLIC_. On Vercel, scope Production vs Preview
# env vars deliberately — Preview deployments must also have real keys.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=""
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=""
CLERK_WEBHOOK_SIGNING_SECRET=""

# ── Dev auth (local only) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Dev-auth mode additionally requires NODE_ENV=development and neither VERCEL
# nor CI to be set. It cannot be enabled in a deployed environment.
ALLOW_DEV_AUTH="false"
# HMAC secret for signing the dev user-switcher cookie. REQUIRED when dev-auth
# mode is active (any random string, e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`) — there is no
# built-in fallback, so a shared dev box can't be spoofed with a known constant.
DEV_AUTH_SECRET=""
